The paper deals with coded caching, which is a technique used in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the design of placement delivery arrays (PDAs), which are used in distributed storage systems (cs.SI) and data centers (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper proposes new centralized coded caching schemes, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and communication complexity (cs.CC).
